# PART C вҖ” Research & Analytics Depth

These additions transform the engine from a backtest runner into a genuine strategy research tool.
They address the **absence of a structured research lifecycle** and add quantitative anti-overfitting
tools that are standard practice in systematic trading.

---

## Gap C1 вҖ” Validation Methodology: New Study Types

**Problem:** Walk-forward uses a single train/test split path. There is no CPCV study, no
anchored walk-forward mode, and no mechanism to enforce a sealed held-out test set.

**Task:** Amend the `StudyType` enum and add two new study types:

```csharp
public enum StudyType {
    MonteCarlo,
    WalkForward,
    AnchoredWalkForward,       // NEW вҖ” keeps training start fixed, expands window
    CombinatorialPurgedCV,     // NEW вҖ” CPCV with PBO metric
    Sensitivity,
    ParameterSweep,
    Realism,
    ParameterStability,
    RegimeSegmentation
}

public enum WalkForwardMode { Rolling, Anchored }
```

### Combinatorial Purged Cross-Validation (CPCV)

CPCV generates all possible combinations of training/test splits across N non-overlapping
folds and measures the **Probability of Backtest Overfitting (PBO)** вҖ” the fraction of paths
where OOS performance is worse than the in-sample median. A robust strategy has a PBO below 5%.
A PBO above 25% is a strong signal of curve-fitting regardless of headline backtest performance.

Surface PBO as a headline metric on the Study Detail screen alongside the existing Robustness Verdict.

### Anchored Walk-Forward

Anchored walk-forward keeps the training start fixed and expands the window вҖ” testing whether
the strategy degrades as more data is added, which more closely mirrors the live-trading scenario.
Add the `WalkForwardMode` field to the walk-forward study configuration; the existing rolling
mode is the default.

### Held-Out Final Test Set

Add a workflow-enforced sealed test set:

1. When a strategy is created, the builder prompts the user to designate the last N% of the
   date range as a sealed test set (recommended: 20вҖ“30%, minimum 1 year).
2. The sealed set is **locked** вҖ” it cannot be used in walk-forward, sensitivity, or parameter sweeps.
3. It is available only via a one-time **"Final Validation"** run, clearly labelled.
4. After a Final Validation run, the strategy is marked as `"Validated"`. Further parameter changes
   trigger: "You have already run a Final Validation. Changing parameters invalidates it."

Add **REQ-V4-21: Advanced Validation Study Types** with acceptance criteria:
(a) CPCV study type is available and surfaces PBO,
(b) Walk-Forward supports rolling and anchored modes,
(c) sealed test set can be designated in the Strategy Builder,
(d) Final Validation is a distinct one-time action with appropriate warnings.

